<HEADLINE> 26 More Die of Gastroenteritis in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 26 (Xinhua) -- A latest outbreak of
gastroenteritis has claimed 26 lives in the past week in Rupandehi
district, western Nepal, the official RSS news agency reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 451 people in the district have been suffering from
the disease with children hardest hit, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Consumption of polluted water and fingerlings was blamed for
the outbreak of the disease, the news agency quoted a local health
officer as saying.
</P>
<P>
Gastroenteritis used to be controlled before mid-September in
the past years, but this year it is still raging in the country at
this time.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that 840 people had succumbed to the
disease from mid-April to October 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
