<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Defeats New Zealand at Dhaka Cricket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sri Lanka scored 191 runs for five in 41.3 overs against 188
of New Zealand in 50 overs at the Bangabandhu National Stadium.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, South Africa became the first team to enter the
semi-finals after beating England at the first quarter-final of
the nine-nation tournament which started here Saturday and will
last till November 2.
</P>
<P>
Sri Land will take on South Africa on October 30 in the first
semi-final of the knock-out event, which is also participated in
by Australia, India, Pakistan, and West Indies.
</P>
<P>
The second semi-final will be played on October 31 between
winners of the other two quarter-finals, to be contested between
Australia and India on Wednesday and between Pakistan and West
Indies on Thursday respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
