<HEADLINE> China's President Pins Hope On New Trade Union Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 26 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting today with newly elected leaders of the All-China
Federation of Trade Unions (ACFTU), said that the Party will
adhere to its basic principle of whole-heartedly depending on the
working class.
</P>
<P>
The meeting at Zhongnanhai, the central government
headquarters, also included some delegates to the recent 13th
National Congress of the ACFTU.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the country faces both opportunities and
challenges in the increasing world multipolarization and economic
globalization and rapid scientific and technological progress.
</P>
<P>
He praised the Chinese working class's role in the past century
and said he hopes they will make fresh contributions to the
reform, opening up and the modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes they support the Party's and government's
major measures in promoting the reform of state-owned enterprises
and have a proper attitude toward the readjustment of interests
relations in the course of the reform.
</P>
<P>
He said that enterprises should improve democratic management
and depend more on workers' representatives meetings to deal with
major issues concerning enterprise reforms and development and
workers' interests.
</P>
<P>
Trade unions should play a greater role as a bridge between the
Party and the workers, he said, and unions should help unite the
workers closely around the Party.
</P>
<P>
He said he also hopes that trade union leaders improve
themselves and try their best to serve the workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
