<HEADLINE> Chinese Government Amends Pharmaceutical Administration Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The National People's Congress
(NPC)'s Education, Science, Culture and Public Health Committee
heard reports here today on an amendment to the Pharmaceutical
Administration Law.
</P>
<P>
Committee members also heard reports on an inspection of the
implementation of the Archives Law and an epidemic prevention law.
</P>
<P>
The committee also reviewed 41 bills submitted by the presidium
of the first session of the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Xiaoyu, Director of the State Bureau of Pharmaceutical
Supervision and Management, said that 14 years of enforcement of
the Pharmaceutical Administration Law has shown that it has played
an important role in guaranteeing the safety of pharmaceuticals
and the detecting of fake products.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the law needs to be amended to be even more
effective.
</P>
<P>
The committee sent fact-finding teams to nine provinces and
municipalities from May to June to check on the implementation of
the Archives Law and found that in some places units did not pay
much attention to the law.
</P>
<P>
In the past two months, the committee also sent a team to
Sichuan, Yunnan and Zhejiang provinces to look into the
implementation of the epidemic prevention law there.
</P>
<P>
The team discovered that some units failed to follow the law
and that the law itself needs to be amended to adapt to the new
situation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
