<HEADLINE> Kunming Horticulture Exposition Implements Exhibition Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 26 (Xinhua) -- A contract signed by Australian
delegates and the organizing committee of the "99 Kunming
Horticulture Exposition" here today meant the implementation of
the committee's plan.
</P>
<P>
The Exposition now has 80 countries and international
organizations that have signed agreements to participate in the
fair.
</P>
<P>
The Association of International Horticultural Producers sent a
telegraph congratulating the Exposition for having broken the
previous record of 70 participants.
</P>
<P>
The "99 Kunming Horticulture Exposition" will be the only large
international event in China before the next century. It is
scheduled for May 1 to October 31, 1999, and will display
horticultural developments worldwide as a sort of "Horticultural
Olympics".
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that the good reaction worldwide comes from two
things: its theme of man and the nature touches all nations, and
Kunming's unique scenery and moderate climate make it a superb
location for this kind of event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
