<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Can Continue Role in Pushing Forward </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Greece could continue to play a
role in pushing forward procedures that would lead to a lasting
peace in the Middle Eastern region, Israeli ambassador in Athens
Ran Curiel said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference on the Israeli-Palestinian
accord, Curiel described Greece's holding of talks between Israeli
and Palestinian MPs in Vouliagmeni and Rhodes recently as positive
for the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Greece could continue in this way to act in the benefit of the
peace process and also support the new process, whether through
the European Union (EU) or through economic means, as Israel lent
particular weight to economic development of the Palestinians, he
said.
</P>
<P>
To help rekindle the stalled Middle East peace process, Greece
has sponsored a series of meetings between Israeli and Palestinian
figures over the past few years with the latest one taking place
on the southern Greek island of Rhodes in July this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
