<HEADLINE> Russian Collision Toll Rises to 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The toll of a collision of three
railway cars and a passenger bus in Far Eastern Russia on Monday
has risen to 22, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident, which also wounded 25 others, happened at an
unmanned railway crossing in Khabarovsk when the three railway
cars loaded with construction materials hit a large Ikarus
passenger bus and split it in half.
</P>
<P>
The cars rode the rails without a locomotive, Tass said,
quoting preliminary information.
</P>
<P>
It said 21 passengers in the bus died instantly in the
collision, and 26 others were hospitalized with injuries. One of
them died in hospital later.
</P>
<P>
Authorities have launched an investigation into the tragedy.
</P>
</TEXT>
