<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-26 17:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinian Body Found; Jewish Settler Shot Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The body of a Palestinian man
was found Monday afternoon outside a Jewish settlement near the
West Bank city of Nablus, Israeli TV Channel One reported.
</P>
<P>
The body was discovered outside Itamar, a Jewish settlement
south of Nablus, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of his death was not immediately known and the
incident was being investigated.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the afternoon, a Jewish settler was shot dead in
another West Bank city of Hebron. Israeli security forces blamed
Palestinians for the killing.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old man, who worked as a security guard at a power
station, was shot in his car near the Jewish settlement of Kiryat
Arba, where he lived. The assailant hurled his body out of the car
before speeding away.
</P>
<P>
A Palestinian journalist found the body and summoned an
ambulance. Palestinian doctors, who rushed to the site trying in
vain to save him, said he had been shot at least twice on the
upper part of the body.
</P>
<P>
Local television quoted a Palestinian source as saying the car
had been located in Palestinian-controlled areas. Palestinian
police joined Israeli security forces in apprehending the attacker.
</P>
<P>
The terror attack was the first since Israeli and Palestinian
leaders signed a land-for-peace deal last Friday at the White
House.
</P>
<P>
Hebron, home to more than 400 Jewish settlers surrounded by
about 120,000 Palestinian residents, has become one of the
flashpoints of conflict.
</P>
<P>
A Jewish settler was stabbed to death in August by a
Palestinian man, who was arrested by Israeli security forces
after throwing two grenades at a bus station in the southern city
of Be'er Sheva injuring 66 people earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
He was said to be also responsible for a grenade attack in
Hebron late September, in which a dozen Israeli soldiers were
injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
