<HEADLINE> 2 Lebanese Civilians Wounded by Israeli Bomb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Two Lebanese civilians were
wounded in southern Lebanon Monday by an Israeli bomb, the Orient
radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The two men were moderately injured when they stepped on
a bomb in the village of Shagran in the central sector of
the Israeli occupied south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese security sources accused Israel of planting the
bomb, saying they have started an investigation into the
incident.
</P>
<P>
Following the explosion, the two injured were taken to a
nearby governmental hospital for treatment, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The fresh casualties have raised to 55 the number of Lebanese
civilians wounded in conflicts between Lebanese guerrillas and
Israeli occupation forces since the start of this year. And 19
others were killed over the same period.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a self-declared security zone in southern
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north
from cross-border attacks by Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, is spearheading a
guerrilla war to try to oust the Israeli troops out of the
country. 
</P>
