<HEADLINE> Schroeder Sworn in as German Chancellor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Gerhard Schroeder was sworn in as
Germany's seventh postwar chancellor on Tuesday after winning an
election vote in Germany's new parliament.
</P>
<P>
The new Bundestag, the lower house of parliament which was
formed on Monday, elected Schroeder by a vote of 351 to 287, with
27 abstentions.
</P>
<P>
He then received a letter of appointment from German President
Roman Herzog and took the oath of office in the Bundestag.
</P>
<P>
"I am very happy and proud," Schroeder said after having been
officially appointed.
</P>
<P>
He told the German president that his new government will not
hesitate to push ahead reforms in order to redress Germany's
economic problems.
</P>
<P>
He also pledged continuity in foreign policy, saying "Fair
partnership with Europe and in trans-Atlantic relations will be
the guidelines of the new government."
</P>
<P>
As Germany's first Social Democrat chancellor after 16 years of
conservative rule under Helmut Kohl, Schroeder will lead a
coalition government with his Social Democratic Party (SPD)
sharing power with the much smaller ecologist Greens party.
</P>
</TEXT>
