<HEADLINE> U.S. Company Sets Up Risk Investment Fund In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The U.S.'s International Data
Group (IDG) and China's Ministry of Science and Technology
announced in Beijing today that they are setting up a risk
investment fund for high technology development in China.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. company will invest one billion U.S. dollars in China's
high-tech enterprises over a 7-year period and provide training
courses on market analysis, program assessment, technical products
development, and investment management.
</P>
<P>
Deng Nan, vice-minister of science and technology, expressed
her support for IDG's move and pledged to make a greater effort to
develop high-tech industries in China through information
exchanges and personnel training with the U.S. company.
</P>
</TEXT>
