<HEADLINE> EU Issues Declaration on Peru-Ecuador Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) issued
a declaration here on Tuesday praising an agreement reached
between Peru and Ecuador to end a border dispute.
</P>
<P>
The declaration said that the EU was greatly satisfied with the
agreement reached on Monday in Brasilia, the capital of Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The EU commended both President Jamil Mahuad of Ecuador and
President Alberto Fujimori of Peru on their personal efforts in
bringing the negotiations to a successful conclusion.
</P>
<P>
It also paid tribute to the congresses and peoples of the two
countries for their contributions to the final settlement.
</P>
<P>
The declaration expressed confidence that the agreement would
contribute to peace and security in the region and to the
well-being of its peoples.
</P>
<P>
Brokered and guaranteed by the United States, Brazil and
Argentina, the peace treaty between Peru and Ecuador was signed to
end a dispute over a 78-kilometer section of common border in the
Andean foothills in the Amazon jungle.
</P>
<P>
The two countries fought wars in 1941, 1981 and 1995 over the
disputed region. Peace talks over the dispute began in 1995.
</P>
