<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Court Insists Counsel Rules as Most Detainees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda (ICTR) insists the
right for assigning counsels for the accused though most of them
joined Monday the on-going hunger strike in their detention
facilities in Arusha, northern Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
An ICTR news release said Tuesday that Le Greffier, registrar
of the ICTR, argued that the assignment of counsel is his
responsibility under the Tribunal's rules as he received a letter
Monday signed by 25 out of the 32 detainees indicating they have
embarked on a hunger strike.
</P>
<P>
"Defense lawyers are assigned to detainees who can not afford
the costs of hiring their own lawyer in order to ensure respect
for the right of the accused to a fair trial," he said. "This
responsibility is acknowledged by the detainees in their letter."
</P>
<P>
The hunger strike was initiated last Thursday by a former
Rwandan mayor who has been convicted of genocide and sentenced to
a life imprisonment by the Tribunal earlier this month for his
role in Rwanda's 1994 massacre.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Paul Akayesu, 45, began his hunger strike to protest the
Tribunal's refusal to assign him the lawyer of his choice, the
Canadian lawyer John Philpot.
</P>
<P>
But Philpot did not apply to be on the Tribunal's list of
approved lawyers, and therefore is ineligible to defend the
convicted mayor on appeal in accordance with the Tribunal's
rules.
</P>
<P>
Akayesu was given a list of six approved lawyers and told to
chose two as his defense counsel, but he refused.
</P>
<P>
The registrar said in the early days of the Tribunal's work,
an attempt was made by a small group of lawyers, mainly from
Canada and Belgium, to monopolize the defense of persons accused
by the Tribunal so that they could determine the course of
events, including blocking the Tribunal's judicial proceedings as
they saw fit.
</P>
<P>
This was a major factor in the Tribunal's decision to
streamline the assignment of defense counsel through the adoption
in January 1996 of the Directive on the Assignment of Defense
Counsel, approved by the Judges in Plenary Session.
</P>
<P>
At present, he said, 41 lawyers from all over the world are
assigned as defense counsel and co-counsel to the detainees. been
assigned, he said.
</P>
<P>
The news release said the registry believes that the on-going
hunger strikes by detainees to pressure the Tribunal are
unwarranted and may indeed be unrelated to the issue of
assignment of defense counsel.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, a spokesman for the Tribunal said the ICTR will not
be pressurized or blackmailed by Akayesu by going on a hunger
strike.
</P>
<P>
However, Kingsley Moghalu said Monday, Akayesu was free to
have a lawyer of his choice if he was prepared to finance his
defense counsel.
</P>
<P>
He added that the UN-court has always respected the rights of
the accused persons "but within the framework of a UN-system and
its established courts."
</P>
<P>
Prison sources said Akayesu has not been taking any solid
food, but was profusely smoking and has access to newspapers and
radio.
</P>
<P>
A total of 35 suspects have been indicted so far by the ICTR,
founded by the United Nations following the Rwanda massacre in
April 1994 soon after President Juvenal Habyarimana, a Hutu, died
when his plane was shot down over the capital Kigali.
</P>
<P>
About 500,000 people, mostly Tutsis and moderate Hutus, were
reportedly killed in the three-month slaughter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981027.0053 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dunhuang's 2,000-Year-Old Spring In Danger Of Drying Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DUNHUANG, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The Crescent Spring has
existed in Gansu province's Dunhuang for more than 2,000 years,
but it now faces the danger of drying up, as its water level keeps
dropping 30 cm every year.
</P>
<P>
Its size has decreased from 1.7 hectares in the 1960s to 0.4
hectare today, according to a Dunhuang Environment Bureau official
and there are now dead trees near the spring.
</P>
<P>
The spring got its name from its appearance and is as much an
attraction as the Mogao Grotto. In more than 2,000 years, it has
never been buried by the moving dunes. Some geologists say that it
was part of the Danghe River in ancient times, but after the river
changed its course, the spring kept supplying water.
</P>
<P>
A reservoir was built on the upper reaches of the Danghe in the
1970s, cutting off some of the subterranean flow to the spring,
the environmental official says.
</P>
<P>
The General Administration of Environmental Protection recently
had a look at the environment of Dunhuang and pointed to the
improper water use in tourism and agriculture as another reason
for the spring's drying up.
</P>
<P>
Dunhuang's annual rainfall is less than 50 mm and the annual
amount of evaporation exceeds 2,400 mm. However, irrigation by
flooding is still very popular in nearby fields, allowing a large
amount of water to evaporate.
</P>
<P>
Dunhuang has more than 100 hotels, but their waste water is not
treated, causing serious waste.
</P>
<P>
No effective ways have been found to keep the spring from
drying up but environmental specialists warn that water use
methods have to be changed in Dunhuang.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
