<HEADLINE> Chairman Of Russian Duma Looking For Cooperation With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Russia's Duma
Gennady Seleznev told a press conference here today that he hopes
to strengthen Russian-Chinese cooperation in the fields of
economy, trade, science and technology and culture.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese place great importance on developing a
strategic and cooperative partnership with Russia and that he
believes that Russia is able to tap its economic, scientific and
technological potential and overcome current economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral cooperation in economy, trade,
science and technology and culture has not been fully explored and
that it is difficult to reach the 20-billion-U.S.-dollar goal
for the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
But, he said, bilateral mutual understanding and respect, and
reciprocal cooperation are more important, and the Russian
parliament and government will make an effort to reach that goal.
</P>
<P>
He praised China's achievements in reforms and opening up and
said that China's reforms have contributed to the growing of
national strength and the improvements in people's lives.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia and China have cooperated well in nuclear
energy and military technology and that there is still vast
potential for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Duma will push for overall development of a bilateral
strategic and cooperative partnership, he said. 
</P>
