<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets OPCW Director-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen met
here today with the Director-General of the Organization for the
Prohibition of Chemical Weapons Jose Bustani.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the Chinese government supports the goals of the
Convention on the Prohibition of the Development, Production,
Stockpiling and Use of Chemical Weapons and on Their Destruction
and will cooperate with the OPCW and all signatory states.
</P>
<P>
The convention is a major event in global arms control and
disarmament and an important step toward the ultimate elimination
of all weapons of mass destruction, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Bustani discussed the work OPCW has done since the Convention
took effect a year and half ago, and said he values China's
contribution to signing and implementing it.
</P>
<P>
Bustani is making his first trip to China at the invitation of
China's Foreign Ministry. He will also meet with Foreign Minister
Tang Jiaxuan and visit Shanghai and Nanjing. 
