<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Leaders Call for Cooperation Between </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait's parliament
reconvened Tuesday morning after a summer recess with top leaders
calling for constructive cooperation between the legislative and
executive authorities, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inauguration of the third annual session of
the National Assembly's eighth term, Emir Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber
Al-Sabah said "we open the session wishing constructive
cooperation from all of you away from whatever could affect our
