He also urged parliament and cabinet members attending the
session to employ "strenuous efforts to strengthen our economy,
develop our reserves and to have our full will away from the
hegemony of any foreign country."
</P>
<P>
In his speech to the assembly, Crown Prince and Prime Minister
Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Salem Al-Sabah reiterated the
government's keenness on cooperation between the two authorities
and the importance of collective work.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between the legislative and executive is
believed to be vital during this session since they have been at
odds over a number of issues including a government proposal to
raise services charges and defense deals with foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
During last session, a grilling motion against Interior
Minister Sheikh Mohammad Al-Sabah by some parliament members
sparked a major confrontation between the executive and
legislative. The cooperation crisis ended almost in a parliament
dissolution.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local media reports said Tuesday that the current
session would start under growing pressure to tackle unpopular
economic reforms aimed at improving state finances and boosting a
sagging stock market.
</P>
<P>
Persistent low oil prices have prompted the government to
consider a raise of charges to some heavily-subsidized services
like water, power, health care and local communication in an
effort to increase revenues, a measure opposed by many MPs.
</P>
</TEXT>
