<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Strengthens Against U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian rupiah was closed at
7,275/7,375 rupiah against the U.S. dollar in the Jakarta
inter-bank spot market on Tuesday, strengthened compared with
Monday's close of 7,500/7,700 rupiah to the greenback.
</P>
<P>
A dealer with an European bank said the rupiah's gain came on
continued selling of U.S. dollars by the central bank Bank
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Some dealers said a report on intervention trading bank also
gave rupiah a boost in trading. It was reported that Bank
Indonesia will use a band when the rupiah exchange rate reaches a
level between 5,000 to 6,000 per dollar.
</P>
<P>
However, Bank Indonesia director Miranda Goeltom had said the
central bank had no plan to restore a rupiah intervention band.
</P>
<P>
"We haven't made any decisions yet. We don't want to do things
in a rush if it is not needed. We certainly will study all
alternatives," she said.
</P>
<P>
"It's part of the research division's job to study various
possibilities. But it does not necessarily mean that we will
implement what we have studied," she added.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah, which hit an eight-month high of 7,150 last
Wednesday, slid back to 7,800 on Thursday and to 7,850 on Friday
following a controversial statement by Coordinating Minister for
Economy, Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita.
</P>
<P>
Ginandjar said the ideal level of the rupiah-U.S. dollar
exchange rate would be between 7,000 and 8,000 to maintain the
competitiveness of the country's exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
