<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Saudi Arabia Welcome Mideast Peace Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Saudi Arabia
have welcomed the latest Palestinian-Israeli accord towards
restoring the Middle East peace process to its proper track.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique issued at the end of a three-day official
visit to Pakistan by Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah Bin Abdul Aziz,
the two sides hoped that the recently signed agreement will
constitute a step towards restoring the peace process to its
proper track.
</P>
<P>
They further expressed the hope that the international
community will play an effective role to bring about Israeli
adherence to its commitments under various peace accords.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Saudi Arabia also called in the communique for the
resumption of the Syrian-Israeli talks and the prompt
implementation of the U.N. Security Council Resolution 425
concerning southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi crown prince arrived in Lahore, Pakistan's second
largest city, on Sunday for a three-day official visit at the
invitation of Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, the crown prince held extensive talks with
Sharif on matters relating to bilateral relations and regional
situation, with particular reference to the Arab and Muslim world,
and the international developments at large.
</P>
<P>
The joint communique said the two sides agreed that the
establishment of peace and security in South Asia required non-use
of force and peaceful settlement of disputes, especially the Jammu
and Kashmir dispute, which should be finally settled in accordance
with the U.N. resolution.
</P>
<P>
The two sides expressed satisfaction over the steady growth of
their collaboration in various fields. They reiterated their
determination to intensify cooperation in the economic and
technological fields to make it commensurate with the level and
quality of bilateral political relations.  
</P>
