<HEADLINE> Chinese Lawmakers Want To Add Continental Shelf Law To HKSAR Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Chairpersons of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC) delivered a
draft to the Ninth NPC Standing Committee for the Exclusive
Economic Zone (EEZ) and Continental Shelf Law to be included in
Appendix 3 of the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The chairpersons said that, according to the basic law,
China's national laws, except for Appendix 3, do not apply to the
HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee can add or reduce the number of laws
included in Appendix 3 after consulting with its Committee on the
HKSAR Basic Law and the government of HKSAR. All laws in Appendix
3 must be on national defense and foreign affairs, and other laws
that do not concern the autonomy of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The EEZ and Continental Shelf Law, which was adopted by the
Third Meeting of the Ninth NPC Standing Committee in April, is a
national defense and foreign affairs law and is outside the
autonomy of the HKSAR, thus it needs to be included in Appendix 3.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR Basic Law Committee, which is affiliated to the NPC
Standing Committee, and the HKSAR government have agreed to
include the law in Appendix 3 of the Basic Law of the
HKSAR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
