<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Legislators Need To Study Contract Law Draft More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Gu Angran, vice-chairman of the
Law Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC), said
here today that a Contract Law draft needs further study.
</P>
<P>
Gu told the 5th meeting of the 9th NPC Standing Committee that
the draft should describe certain losses caused by changing
situations and pointed out that it should say whether a person can
demand a change or cancellation of the contract.
</P>
<P>
Gu said that two laws on economic contracts allow for increased
fines for a breach of contract if the compensation is not enough
to cover losses, and the legislators will study how to handle this
matter.
</P>
<P>
The draft states that real estate contracts must be in written
form, and contracts involving foreign traders and payments
exceeding 100,000 yuan (about 12,000 U.S. dollars) must also be
written form, Gu said.
</P>
<P>
However, just which contracts and how much a contract should
contain for payment needs further study, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
