<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Satellite TV Channel to Be Launched Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 27 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN senior officials laid
the basis for launching an ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian
Nations) satellite TV channel next year as they ended a two-day
meeting here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the preparatory meeting for the implementation of the ASEAN
satellite channel, participating ASEAN officials responsible for
information agreed on the launch time of the channel and the
operational and financial details for the channel which has been
projected for presenting their points of view to the region and
beyond.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was a follow-up to the 5th ASEAN Ministers
Responsible for Information Conference held in Bangkok, Thailand,
in July this year.
</P>
<P>
The officials also agreed that member countries would each make
a fixed annual contribution to the operation of the Channel.
</P>
<P>
Singapore International Media has been picked up as the network
coordinator who will choose its own satellite operator based on
commercial and technical considerations as long as the broadcast
covers all ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
Under their agreement, the channel will broadcast for six to
eight hours per day and programs will comprise news and current
affairs, entertainment, lifestyle, sports and education which will
be contributed by members.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the agreement, members will be allowed to
downlink and rebroadcast the channel domestically either through
cable or terrestrial TV, or their own Direct-to-Home
infrastructure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
