<HEADLINE> Volleyball Congress : Negotiating Change for Next Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Over 220 delegates from some 160
National Federations out of the record 217 total affiliates will
begin to discuss the future of their sport on Wednesday when the
26th World Congress of world volleyball's ruling body FIVB opens.
</P>
<P>
During the 3-day Congress, held every two years, fundamental
decisions will be made, especially concerning the rules of the
game in order to adapt Volleyball to the next century and meet
the demands of participants, spectators and media.
</P>
<P>
The organisers of the most important FIVB events on schedule
next year will be making presentation to the Congress: World Cup
in Japan, and World Championships for men's youth in Saudi
Arabia, women's youth in Portugal, men's junior in Thailand and
women's junior in Dominican Republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
