<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets With Laotian Vice-Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Defense Minister Chi Haotian,
in a meeting today with the visiting Laotian Vice-Minister of
Defense Nakhone Sisanonh, said that the two countries are linked
by rivers and mountains and that they have a long-standing
traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two have increased exchanges and cooperation
since they normalized relations in 1991 and that there is a solid
foundation for further cooperation between the two countries and
their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and armed forces are willing to engage
in all-round and multi-ply cooperation with their Laotian
counterparts, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sisanonh thanked China for its support to Laos in the past
several decades and that the Laotian Party, government and people
will never forget it. The Laotian armed forces will reinforce
cooperation with the PLA, he said.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the PLA General Staff, held
talks with Sisanonh on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Laotian guests arrived in Beijing on Sunday.  
</P>
