<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Launches Joint Operation to Flush out Illegal Immigrants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong government has
launched a territory-wide operation against illegal immigration
and arrested 195 people.
</P>
<P>
The operation, jointly mounted by the Police, Immigration
Department and Labor Department of Hong Kong, was part of the
government's continuous effort to flush out illegal immigrants, a
government announcement said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 130 suspected illegal immigrants arrested by the Police
have been referred to the Immigration Department, and those found
to be illegal immigrants will be repatriated, the announcement
said.
</P>
<P>
During the 24-hour operation ended at 5 am Tuesday, the Police
stepped up their identification spot checks in public places and
carried out checks at suspicious locations throughout the
territory.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman reiterated that there was no question of
any amnesty for illegal immigrants.
</P>
<P>
"Our latest operation should drive home the point that there
will be no change to this policy. Anyone foolish enough to believe
otherwise is only cheating oneself," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman stressed that apart from continuous checks
throughout the territory, there was no let-up in anti-illegal
immigration efforts at the border.
</P>
<P>
"A high state of vigilance will continue to be maintained by
the Police and the security forces both at the land and sea
borders," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
