<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 1.51 percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed 1.51
percent higher Tuesday, driven by active derivative-related buying
before the expiration of the October index futures on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index gained 148.14 points to end the
day at 9,927.05. Turnover was 6.026 billion HK dollars (772
million u.s. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Since the market will close Wednesday for Chung Yeung Festival,
heavy short-covering occurred Tuesday, the last trading day before
this month's index futures expire on Thursday, according to broke
dealers.
</P>
<P>
Property shares led the advance by surging 324.31 points, or
2.59 percent, followed by an across-the-board rise in banking,
utility, commerce and industry stocks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
