<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombian Climber Missing in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Colombian climber Lenin
Granados went missing Monday in a big avalanche on Mount Manaslu
in Nepal, the Nepali Ministry of Tourism and Civil Aviation said
in a press release Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that the avalanche occurred when 31-year-old
Granados and his four teammates were going down from Camp II
(6,000m) to Camp I (5,900m) .
</P>
<P>
Due to bad weather, the seven-member team decided to abandon
their bid on the 8,163-meter peak, the eighth highest in the
world, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The team led by Cristobal Von Rothkirch, a 35-year-old
photographer, tried to conquer the peak from the traditional
northeast face, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the rescue operation has been unsuccessful
because the area is extremely dangerous and inaccessible.
</P>
</TEXT>
