<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Port Equipment Exhibition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The largest exhibition of
technology and equipment for harbor construction opened today in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition has attracted representatives from over 100
major ports and companies in Germany, the United States, Britain,
the Netherlands, Italy, Australia, Japan, China and the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The event features technology and equipment in the fields of
shipbuilding, navigation, dredging and harbor construction.
</P>
<P>
China has 130 ports which play host to 36,000 ships from over
100 countries and regions a year. Their annual handling capacity
totaled 1.3 billion tons last year. The country's container
transport has grown at an annual increase rate of 25 percent for
12 years.
</P>
<P>
To sustain its rapid economic growth, China plans to build 100
deep-water berths accommodating 10,000 dwt ships in the next two
or three years and raise its port handling capacity by 200 million
tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
