<DOCNO> XIE19981027.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Islamic Court Chairman Kidnaped in Mogadishu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The citizens of the Somali
capital were struck Tuesday by a terrifying incident against the
efforts of restoring the law and order in Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Omar Moallim Nur, the chairman of the Shirkoleh Islamic
court was abducted by four unidentified gunmen early Tuesday
morning near his house in South Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, the gunmen stopped Sheikh Omar and
ordered him to ride with them in a FIAT 131 car they were driving
and sped away firing no shots.
</P>
<P>
Later reports said Sheikh Omar was taken to Sigaleh area of
Bermuda vicinity, one of Mogadishu's most dangerous areas in the
heart of the capital, where well-armed gunmen have been operating
since the beginning of the civil war.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Islamic court were seen getting ready in
their headquarters with their battle wagons and gunmen in case
any trace is found.
</P>
<P>
Neither the identity of the gunmen nor the reason behind the
abduction is known. However, some sources said the gunmen are
just the remaining of a group whose malicious activities were
seriously handicapped by the Islamic Court after many of their
fellow friends were arrested, while others have run for exile
after the threat and pressure on them was increased.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen in Bermuda area have been responsible for the
kidnaping of many Somalis since beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
The incident followed an armed confrontation between two rival
militiamen near the Black Sea junction of South Mogadishu Monday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
At least four people were wounded including two school girls
in their uniforms after gunmen driving two battle wagons attacked
a communication center near Black Sea junction.
</P>
<P>
The assault was reportedly a retaliation move by the attacking
gunmen who have lost one of their fellow sub-clan men to the
owners of the communication facility in the same area a day
earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
