<HEADLINE> WBC Boss Called for Probe into World Boxing Bodies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He urged an investigation into all so-called international
boxing organizations, and said they had to prove the validity of
their alleged world status.
</P>
<P>
Opening the annual WBC convention in Johannesburg at the
presence of former amateur boxer, South African President Nelson M
andela, Sulaiman said: "It is time to stop deceiving the boxing
fans of the world."
</P>
<P>
"Most of these champions, with all due respect, are not
champions of the world," he said. "Those organizations are
selling to the people a lie, and to sell a lie is nothing but a
fraud."
</P>
<P>
"Let us stop it for the sake of credibility, for the sake of
the respect that the sport of boxing deserves," Sulaiman said.
</P>
<P>
Calling for a probe into the validity of all world boxing
controlling bodies, he said that if action was not taken soon,
"boxing will die in 50 years, and will become merely a
circus".
</P>
<P>
Sulaiman also urged the establishment of a fund so that boxing
could provide pension "for our heroes of the past".
</P>
<P>
