<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Sends More Troops to Crisis-Torn Warri </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government has sent
more troops including units of the Amphibious Brigade to Warri to
beef up military presence in the crisis-torn town, This Day
newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
About 500 soldiers arrived last Sunday at the Warri airstrip
where arrangements were being made to airlift them to the coastal
area.
</P>
<P>
An officer at David Ejoor Barracks in Effurun near Warri was
quoted as saying that most of the soldiers would be deployed in
the Riverine areas to protect oil installations.
</P>
<P>
The reinforcement of troops in Warri followed the escalation
of the mayhem in the area last Saturday when the Itsekiri
ancestral home and the Olu's alternate palace were allegedly
razed by Ijaw youths who also sacked two police stations and took
all the policemen hostage.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian government condemned at the weekend the renewed
hostilities between the Ijaws and Itsekiris, saying that it will
no longer tolerate any act of lawlessness.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers were probably being taken to flush out Ijaw
youths who are still laying siege to some oil flow stations, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Non native residents in Warri and the surrounding trouble
spots have fled the area following the attack by Ijaw youths last
Saturday on the ancestral home of the Itsekiris.
</P>
<P>
The non natives' fear heightened when a Yoruba boat captain
was shot by some Ijaws for allegedly scolding an Ijaw youth.
</P>
<P>
The Ijaws and Itsekiris have been engaged in communal clashes
since 1996 over the relocation of the headquarters of the Warri
south local government from Ogbe-Ijo (an Ijaw settlement) to
Ogidegben (an Itsekiri settlement).
</P>
<P>
Hostilities between them were rekindled about 10 days ago when
the Ijaws were alleged to have interrupted the funeral procession
of an Itsekiri chief and kidnaped his son and some others.
</P>
<P>
The Delta State Government last Friday imposed a dusk to dawn
curfew on Warri and its environs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
