<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Tuesday due to lack of fresh
leads.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was down
3.15 points to 415.96, the all-share Emas Index shed 1.10 points
to 108.20, the Industrial Index lost 3.23 points to 804.21 and the
Second Board Index dropped 1.75 points to 99.74.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmed gainers by 490 to 108 while 120 counters
were unchanged, 199 untraded and 43 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover declined to 114.711 million shares valued at
203.399 million ringgit (53.526 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 131.807 million shares valued at 237.121 million ringgit
(62.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Main Board turnover fell to 107.487 million shares valued
at 191.842 million ringgit (50.484 million U.S. dollars) from
123.751 million valued at 224.278 million ringgit (59.02 million
U.S. dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board volume declined to 7.224 million shares valued
at 11.557 million ringgit (3.041 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 8.056 million shares valued at 12.843 million ringgit
(3.379 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, off-market deals soared to 14.291 million shares
valued at 27.081 million ringgit (7.126 million U.S. dollars) from
3.206 million shares valued at 8.601 million ringgit (2.263
million U.S. dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products contributed 6.253
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products 8.327
million shares, construction 12.436 million shares, trade/services
30.941 million shares, infrastructure 1.035 million shares,
finance 16.181 million shares, hotels 364,000 shares, properties
16.111 million shares, plantation 4.779 million shares, mining
249,400 shares, trusts 78,000 shares, closed/fund 55,000 shares
and loans 10.677 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
