<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Jump Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices soared up on
Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as increasing expectations for
further cut in interest rates prevailed over the market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) surged by 40.10 points
to end at 1,153.60 points as a result of frenzied buying on the
bourse.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover increased to 398.72 million units worth
457.70 million Singapore dollars (about 291 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers led losers by 263 to 33 with 124 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Ho Pro topped the active chart with a turnover of 39.72 million
units. KepLand was the second most heavily traded stock on the
exchange with a turnover of 19.10 million shares. SembCorp was
next with 18.16 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
CityDev led the ascent of the day as it rose by 80 cents to
5.90 Singapore dollars at close. UOB F ran up 50 cents to finish
at 7.30 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem was up 45 cents to end at
8.25 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day
with a loss of 30 cents to close at 18.80 Singapore dollars. Times
Pub retreated 15 cents to close at 2.35 Singapore dollars.
Delifrance inched 12 cents lower to end at 1.36 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said interest-rate-sensitive stocks like banks and
properties led the run-up which was fueled by expectations of at
least another 50 basis-point-cut in local interest rates by the
end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Singapore's major banks lowered their prime lending rate by a
quarter percentage point to 7 percent a few weeks ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
