<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on Tokyo International Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Tang Guoqiang said that China hopes that the
international community, especially the developed countries, would
make further efforts to promote Africa's peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remark at a regular press conference here today
when commenting on the Tokyo International Conference on African
Development (TICAD), which ended last week.
</P>
<P>
He said that 80 countries including China and over 40
international organizations including the United Nations sent its
delegations to the conference.
</P>
<P>
The participants discussed the challenge facing African
development, Tang said, adding that this shows the international
community has paid more attention to the continent's development
than before. "This is gratifying," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the international community especially the
developed countries have the obligation of helping Africa
eradicate poverty and promoting its development.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China, as a developing country, has
always supported the effort of the African countries to build
their countries and promote their economies. And over a long
period of time, China has provided the Africa countries, within
its power, with economic, technical, cultural and medical aids.
The recipients have spoken highly of the aids, Tang added.
</P>
<P>
Tang Guoqiang stressed that the aids are mutual between "poor
fiends" and the purpose is to seek common development.
</P>
<P>
The second TICAD was held in Tokyo in October 19-21 and the
first TICAD, in October of 1993, also in Tokyo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
