<P>
CAIRO, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic briefs
from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The European Investment Bank said Monday that it
will lend the Palestinian National Authority some 52 million
U.S. dollars for projects relating to water, transport
infrastructure and tourism, The Jerusalem Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordanian Minister of Water and Irrigation Hani Malki
and Israeli Foreign Minister Ariel Sharon Monday inaugurated a dam
in the southern town of Adasyyeh to increase Jordan's annual
capacity of water diversion from the Yarmouk River to the King
Abdullah Canal from 100 million cubic meters (MCM) to 150 MCMs.
</P>
<P>
The dam is being constructed in line with the Jordanian-Israeli
peace treaty signed four years ago and will be completed in nine
months.
</P>
<P>
MUSCAT -- The Omani Liquified Natural Gas company and the
Japanese "Osaka Gas" company signed an agreement Monday, under
which the Japanese company will purchase 700,000 tonnes of Omani
liquified gas a year.
</P>
<P>
By now, 70 percent of the liquified gas project has been
completed. The project is located in the Omani state of Soor, and
production is expected to begin in 2000. 
