<DOCNO> XIE19981027.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan's September Jobless Rate Stays at Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Japan's unemployment rate
remained at a record high of 4.3 percent in September, unchanged
from August, the Management and Coordination Agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate among men was at a record high of 4.4 percent,
the same as in the previous month, while that among women was 4.2
percent, down 0.1 percentage point from August, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 2.95 million people were without jobs in September,
up 25 percent from a year earlier, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Economists with the agency and with private sectors have agreed
that the jobless figure will likely remain high in the coming
months.
</P>
<P>
This sentiment was bolstered by a separate report also released
Tuesday by the Labor Ministry.
</P>
<P>
In the report, the ministry said the seasonally adjusted ratio
of job offers in September fell to 0.49 -- the lowest level since
the end of World War II -- from 0.50 in August, meaning there were
only 49 job offers for every 100 people looking for work.
</P>
<P>
Japan's jobless rate broke the 4-percent barrier for the first
time in April and has edged up gradually in the months since.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
