<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With Russian Duma Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Since China and Russia are both
big nations with great influence in the world, and neighboring
countries, they should maintain and develop long-term good
neighborly friendship and mutually beneficial cooperation, with a
view to safeguarding the fundamental interests of both nations and
to world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin made the remarks during a meeting with
Gennady Seleznev, chairman of the Russian Duma, here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said friendship and cooperation are not only based on a
consensus reached by Russian and Chinese leaders but represent the
aspirations of the people in both nations.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have greatly enhanced cooperation and
exchanges between various sectors at different levels, he noted.
And there is also an increase in the bilateral exchange of
personnel at various levels.
</P>
<P>
Strong cooperative ties built between the Chinese and Russian
congresses are very important for strengthening Sino-Russian
strategic partnership and consolidating the traditional
friendship, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Seleznev said the Russian Duma is willing to actively advance
the all-round development of Sino-Russian strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
He added that the members of the Duma, and both the Russian
government and people, are looking forward to President Jiang's
forthcoming visit and are fully confident of inevitable
success. Seleznev also briefed Jiang on Russia's domestic
situation.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Chinese president expressed his confidence that
the Russian people will overcome temporary difficulties and embark
on the road of revitalization as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), Zhang Deguang, Chinese
Vice-foreign minister, and Russian Ambassador to China Igor
Rogachev were among those present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua gave a luncheon in honor of Seleznev and his party
today.  
</P>
