<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drilling Starts on Texaco-Financed Coalbed Methane Wildcat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese workers with
Zhongyuan Petroleum Prospecting Administration recently started
drilling on a coalbed methane wildcat with financing from Texaco
Company of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The wildcat, or Sunan-1 Well, is situated in Huaibei City of
east China's Anhui Province. It will be one of the four wildcats
that will be sunk by the administration, based in central China's
Henan Province, for the U.S. company.
</P>
<P>
Texaco has entered its first cooperation with China Coalbed
Methane Co. Ltd. in exploring coalbed methane resources in Huaibei
City.
</P>
<P>
And Zhongyuan Petroleum Prospecting Administration, which has
drilled one third of China's 100 coalbed methane wells, won a public
bidding for sinking the wildcats with financing from the
U.S. company, said information from the administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
