<DOCNO> XIE19981027.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National People's Congress Begins New Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- A number of high profile laws
related to village democracy, adoption, security and
administrative appeals were tabled during today's opening session
of the National People's Congress (NPC), China's highest
legislative body.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, presided over
an explanatory hearing of draft laws during the opening meeting of
the fifth session of the Ninth NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The draft revision to the Basic law on Village Committees,
adopted 10 years ago, strengthens grass roots democracy in
China.
</P>
<P>
The draft provides new rules for handling sensitive and
delicate relations between village committees and Party committee
branches on the village level.
</P>
<P>
It stipulates that grass roots branches of the Chinese
Communist Party (CPC) will assume a leadership role in the rural
work in accordance with the CPC charter and related
regulations. Branches will strictly abide by the Constitution and
national laws to protect the direct democratic rights of villagers
and their self-governing responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
The new draft law on adoption features simplified procedures
for foreigners adopting Chinese children. The first draft required
foreigners to both register with the government and authenticate
documents with notaries of public authorized by the Chinese
government. However, the new draft make the notarization
requirement optional depending on the desires of either one or
both parties.
</P>
<P>
The Security Act, which was drafted six years ago, was
resubmitted for a fourth review. Lawmakers noted that lessons
learned from the international financial crisis were summerized
and are reflected in the new draft.
</P>
<P>
A number of chapters and clauses are devoted to strengthening
the government's supervisory and regulatory powers over the
securities market, risk protection and protecting the interests of
investors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981027.0142 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
