<HEADLINE> Japan, Kyrgyzstan to Strengthen Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Japan and Kyrgyzstan on Tuesday
inked a joint statement on friendship and cooperation, calling for
the expansion of bilateral ties in political, economic and
cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
The statement was signed by Japanese Prime Minister Keizo
Obuchi and visiting Kyrgyzstan President Askar Akaev.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, Japan welcomed Kyrgyzstan's progress in its
democratization and creation of a market-oriented economy, while
Kyrgyzstan encouraged Japan to increase its development aid to the
central Asian country.
</P>
