<DOCNO> XIE19981027.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National People's Congress Beings New Session (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The focus of attention in the economic arena has centered on
formulating the nation's first contract law. However, lawmakers
are still debating several key issues, including how to handle the
breaches of contract resulting from changes in national policy,
compensation for losses beyond the financial terms of a contract,
and the applicability of verbal and written contracts.
</P>
<P>
The draft law on administrative appeals represents a major part
of anti-corruption and human rights legislation. The draft
condenses procedures for public appeals to the government
concerning violations of the legal rights and interests of
citizens and legal entities. The government is expected to adopt
the law which will provide a highly effective supervisory
mechanism.
</P>
<P>
Lawmakers will also review the draft law on military service
which will reduce the existing 3-4 year compulsory military
service to only two years. China currently has a volunteer
military service system and the draft law includes a stipulation
banning extended service for draftees.
</P>
<P>
The State Council submitted the amended Highway Law which
integrates various highway fees with state automobile sales and
fuel taxes.
</P>
<P>
The amended law is expected to help to curb the arbitrary
collection of highway fees and relive motor vehicle operators of
excessive changes.
</P>
<P>
In a rare move, leaders of the NPC Standing Committee tabled a
bill calling implementation of the National Law on Exclusive
Economic Zones and the Continental Shelf in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Deputies adopted a decision to fill a vacancy left after the
death of Deputy Liu lit-for.
</P>
<P>
An additional three international and bilateral treaties were
also submitted for deliberation and approval. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
