<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 19 Tamil rebels killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Sunday killed 19 Tamil rebels in north and east of the country,
military spokesman here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said government troops conducted a small group
operation ahead of defenses in north west of Paranthan Monday
morning. The troops engaged a rebel bunker line with mortars,
completely destroying the bunkers.
</P>
<P>
At least 12 terrorists were killed and several others were
injured in the fighting, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident Monday during daytime at Verugal in
Tricomalee district, on information received about terrorist
movements, troops engaged the area with artillery fire, troops
confirmed seven rebels were killed and eight others injured due to
the artillery fire, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a war against the government
since 1983 for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
