<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Meets Sierra Leonean Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan met here today with Sierra Leonean Minister of Foreign
Affairs and Cooperation Sama Banya.
</P>
<P>
Tang said China cherishes its traditional friendship with
Sierra Leone and hopes to solidify and develop the friendship.
</P>
<P>
China also is ready to work together with Sierra Leone in an
effort to protect the legal rights and interests of developing
nations.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders exchanged of views on bilateral ties and
various other matters of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the two countries have engaged in extensive
cooperation in political, economic, cultural, educational and
health fields since the establishment of diplomatic relations some
27 years ago.
</P>
<P>
China and Sierra Leone have also cooperated and supported each
other in the international arena, said Tang.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese government sincerely appreciates
Sierra Leone's adherence to the "one China" policy, Tang noted.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader also expressed appreciation for progress in
Sierra Leone's peace process.
</P>
<P>
Tang briefed the Sierra Leonean delegation on the current
political and economic situation in China.
</P>
<P>
Banya pointed out the numerous examples of cooperation between
China and Sierra Leone throughout his nation. He said "Sierra
Leone will always adhere to its 'one China' stance regardless of
whatever might happen."
</P>
<P>
The Sierra Leonean delegation arrived in China on October 26 at
the invitation of Tang.  
</P>
