<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, October 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME -- Italian Prime Minister Massino D'Alema Monday urged the
majority caucuses in the senate to adopt exceptional fast track
procedures to ensure "very rapid" approval of the 1999 budget,
saying the budget is one of his government's three basic
priorities.
</P>
<P>
"We are already almost beyond the statutory limit, but we must
do all we can to get back within the timetable," he said. "To do
this, an exceptional procedure is needed." (Italy-Prime
Minister-Budget)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori and his
Ecuadoran counterpart Jamil Mahuad on Monday signed a landmark
peace treaty ending a 57-year bloody border dispute between the
two neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The signing of the pact is seen as highly significant for Latin
America, bringing together two rivals in an example which should
be followed throughout the region and the world. Under the pact,
Peru ceded a 100-hectare hill area to Ecuador. (Peru-Ecuador-Peace
Pact)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PRAGUE -- A Czech military helicopter on a peace-keeping
mission in Bosnia crashed Sunday, killing all three crew members
on board, the Defense Ministry said Monday.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Czech Defense Ministry told reporters that
the MI-17 helicopter was flying from Bosnia to Split in Croatia.
It lost contact with the ground control soon after taking off and
crashed over the west of Bosnia. (Czech-Helicopter-Crash) 
</P>
