<HEADLINE> 23rd International Quality Convention Opened In Sri </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 27 (Xinhua) -- The ceremonial opening of the
23rd International Convention on Quality Control Circles (ICQCC)
was opened here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony, the president of Sri Lanka Association for the
Advancement of Quality and Productivity (SLAAQP) Sunil Wijesinghe
said quality circles which originated in Japan in the 1960's,
became very popular first in Southeast Asia, then in other parts
of Asia and later on, spread all over the world. It is becoming
very popular in Sri Lanka as well.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that now the ICQCC is the most popular
international convention among professionals who have dedicated
their work towards improving quality.
</P>
<P>
Attending the opening ceremony were Over 300 foreign delegates
from different countries and areas, including China, Chinese
Taiwan, Japan, India, Philippines, Malaysia, Singapore, Bangladesh
and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The Organizers have arranged two seminars During the convention
which will be closed on October 29.
</P>
<P>
Since 1976, the ICQCC holds one meeting annually. 
