<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets Finnish Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today expressed great satisfaction with the development of the
Sino-Finnish relations during a meeting with visiting Finnish
Prime Minister Paavo Lipponen.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that great changes have taken place over the past
50-odd years and pointed out that China and Finland have
maintained a long relationship based on mutual trust and
respect. He said frequent meetings between leaders from the two
nations have helped promote friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The the two countries will celebrate the 50th anniversary of
the establishment of bilateral diplomatic ties at the turn of
the century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said China and Finland have complementary economies and
have actively engaged in scientific and technological,
educational, cultural and military exchanges.
</P>
<P>
"China is delighted with the positive development trend in the
Sino-Finnish ties," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He described Finland as a beautiful country and praised the
hospitality of Finnish people. Finland is famous for its
metallurgy and papermaking technology, said Jiang, who also noted
the popularity of Nokia telecommunications equipment in China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang asked Lipponen to convey his best regards to his Finnish
counterpart, Martti Ahtisaari.
</P>
<P>
He said China highly values cooperation with the European
Union, and the advancement in Sino-EU ties in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The joint declaration China and the EU signed earlier this year
provided a mechanism for expanding meetings between the two sides,
said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Finland will chair the European Union next year,
Jiang said China believes Finland will play an important role in
spurring the development of Sino-EU ties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang briefed Lipponen on China's current economic
situation. He pointed out that China's rural economy has developed
smoothly and rural living standards have continued to rise since
the adoption of the reform and opening policies some 20 years
ago. He also reiterated China will steadfastly adhere to the
policies.
</P>
<P>
Lipponen pointed to his highly constructive talks with Premier
Zhu Rongji on Monday.
</P>
<P>
He expressed confidence that bilateral cooperation will enter
a new phase as the the two nations celebrate the 50th anniversary
of diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
President Ahtisaari visited China in 1996 and the two countries
agreed to double their trade volume within three years, said
Lipponen, adding that Finland is determined to fulfil the goal.
</P>
<P>
He noted the fact that the number of Finnish businessmen in the
delegation fully demonstrates Finland's willingness to consolidate
bilateral trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Finland and China should play their due roles as stablizing
factors in the international community, and commit themselves to
ensuring world peace and stability, according to Lipponen.
</P>
<P>
He said Finland will assume the rotating position of EU
chairman next year and will continue to contribute to the
advancement of EU-Chinese ties.
</P>
<P>
Lipponen praised the rural economic development and noted that
the efforts of 1.2 billion Chinese people will ensure the
availability of adequate food and clothing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
