<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2 on
the Richter Scale hit Ninglang Yi Autonomous County, home of the
Yi Nationality in southwest China's Yunnan Province, at 04:01
(Beijing Time) on October 27, according to the State Seismological
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The quake destroyed houses in certain areas and authorities are
currently attempting to determine the total extent of the damage
in terms of casualties and property damage. No deaths have been
reported.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was located at 27.2 degrees north
latitude and 101.0 degrees east longitude. The tremors could be
felt throughout Ninglang, as well as in Yanyuan, Sichuan Province,
and various other nearby regions.
</P>
<P>
The quake is the second in the Ninglang area this month, with
the first quake measuring 5.3 degrees on the Richter Scale hitting
the area on October 2.  
</P>
</TEXT>
