<HEADLINE> Italian FM Calls on Cooperation With Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Costa Rica should
strengthen cooperation in cracking down on drug-smuggling, said
Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini Monday.
</P>
<P>
In meeting with his Costa Rican counterpart Roberto Rojas
Lopez, Dini said the two countries should cooperate in combating
drug-trafficking and organized crime.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged their views on reform of the United Nations,
preparations for the upcoming summit of the European Union and
Latin American-Caribbean nations, the financial crisis as well as
the economic integration process in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also discussed the possibility of cooperation
in infrastructure, culture and university training between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Rojas came here from Portugal where he had attended the annual
Iberian-American summit. 
