<HEADLINE> NPC to Fill Vacancy for One Hong Kong Deputy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- China's highest legislative
body has decided to fill the vacancy for one deputy from the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
The decision, which was announced today during the fifth
meeting of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), stipulates that unelected candidates in the
December 8, 1997 election for HKSAR deputies to the Ninth NPC
will fill vacancies in accordance with the number of votes they
received.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR has elected 36 NPC deputies in accordance with
election rules adopted during the fifth session of the Eighth
NPC. The death of Deputy Liu Lit-for created a vacancy shortly
after the election.
</P>
<P>
An explanation from the NPC leadership pointed out that the
Presidium for the Conference for Electing HKSAR Deputies to the
Ninth NPC conducted a preliminary election involving 54
candidates. Thirty-six deputies were eventually elected.
</P>
<P>
The NPC leadership determined that that vacancies would be
filled by unelected candidates in the previous election in
accordance to the number of votes received.  
</P>
</TEXT>
