<HEADLINE> Universities in Shanghai Play Key Role in Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 27 (Xinhua) -- High-tech personnel from
Shanghai universities are playing an increasingly important role
in local industrial technological development.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between enterprises and universities emerged in
1988 and has since strongly promoted technological development in
the city's industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
The city has carried out 260 key technological development
projects in recent years, with some 133 completed by local
universities and colleges.
</P>
<P>
Industrial enterprises in the city have established 43
technological development centers involving local universities and
research institutions.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Automobile Manufacturing Group, one of the first
enterprises to enter into related cooperative ventures, has
provided some 60 million yuan to construct 16 technology centers
since 1994.
</P>
<P>
Long-term steady cooperation between enterprises and
universities has provided leverage enabling parties involved to
share the advantageous use of resources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
