<HEADLINE> Argentina to Increase Investment in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Argentina will triple
its investments in Brazil in the next two years, the Folha de Sao
Paulo daily said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Argentine investments in Brazil will total 3.5 billion U.S.
dollars in the 1998-2000 period, tripling its investments over the
past seven years, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
It added that between 1990 and 1997, Argentina invested over
one billion dollars in various sectors in Brazil, mainly in the
construction, food and beverage industries.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, Brazilian companies invested 1.3 billion
dollars in Argentina, it said, adding that they intended to invest
1.4 billion more until 2000. 
</P>
