<HEADLINE> Shanghai Plans Expanded Ties With Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai plans to strengthen
economic ties with the coastal province of Fujian, according to
Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi.
</P>
<P>
Xu recently visited Fujian and said that economic cooperation
will promote the full use of capital and technology in Shanghai
and natural resources in Fujian. He said cooperation will focus on
development of the high technology industry, asset restructuring
and the modernization of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Both Shanghai and Fujian are relatively highly developed areas
with high technological levels, said Xu, adding that local
governments will engage in joint efforts to establish high-tech
industrial centers. A network system linking Shanghai with various
other provinces, including Fujian, is currently under construction.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has adopted a number of policies designed to attract
enterprise groups in order to help reorganize industrial assets
and promote transregional trade and cooperation, according to Xu.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai and Fujian offer unique advantages which will promote
agricultural modernization, according to Xu. For example, Fujian
offers excellent climate for growing flowers and Shanghai is one
of the country's largest markets for related products.  
</P>
