<HEADLINE> Uruguayan President Meets Chinese Army Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan President Julio
Maria Sanguinetti met Fu Quanyou, chief of the General Staff of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We see with pleasure that China has taken the correct path and
plays a balancing role in international affairs," Sanguinetti told
General Fu.
</P>
<P>
Fu extended greetings to Sanguinetti on behalf of Chinese
President Jiang Zemin and said that relations between the two
countries have been enhanced.
</P>
<P>
He also met with Vice-President Hugo Fernandez Faingold,
Defense Minister Juan Luis Storace and the commanders of the
infantry, navy and air force.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese army chief arrived in Montevideo on Sunday on a
one-day visit to Uruguay following his trip to Argentina and
Peru. He is scheduled to head for Brazil on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
