<HEADLINE> Highlights of Beijing-based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting yesterday with newly
elected leaders of the All-China Federation of Trade Unions
(ACFTU), said that the Party will adhere to its basic principle of
whole-heartedly depending on the working class.
</P>
<P>
He praised the Chinese working class' role in the past century
and said workers would make fresh contributions to the reform,
opening up and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
-- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of China's
National People's Congress (NPC), held talks yesterday afternoon
in Beijing with Gennady Seleznev, chairman of the Duma of Russia
who is here as Li's guest.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Chinese President Jiang Zemin and his Russian
counterpart Boris Yeltsin have met many times, which has
established the guiding principle for the bilateral relations and
laid foundation for developing bilateral good-neighborly and
friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
He said China will join Russia in making an effort to bring
about more results in bilateral parliamentary exchanges.
</P>
<P>
-- The daily says in an article that provinces and autonomous
regions in China should learn from the Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region in its thrifty arrangements for its 40th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
It says that Ningxia has set an example for the whole country
in saving state funds for the 40th anniversary of the region, on
October 25, and asked officials at various levels to cut out all
unnecessary meetings, especially celebrations, receptions,
parties, symposiums, news conferences, and to use the money
instead for economic construction and for solving problems in
people's lives.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji, in a meeting with Finnish Prime
Minister Paavo Lipponen yesterday in Beijing, said that China is
ready to make a concerted effort with Finland to promote bilateral
cooperation in the fields of political affairs, economy, trade,
science, technology, culture and education.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers discussed bilateral ties and other
issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
-- A forum was held on Monday in Beijing's Great Hall of the
People to mark the centenary of the birth of Liu Fei, a former
Vice-Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), who died in 1983.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, Chairman of the National Committee of the CPPCC,
attended the forum.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The accelerated development of high technology and the
modernization of agriculture are top priorities for China's
scientific departments in the next century, said Zhu Lilan,
Minister of Science and Technology. The ministry will step up
research and development programs to help achieve the targets.
</P>
<P>
-- Specialists on women issues from China and Europe have
joined hands yesterday in Beijing to further promote equality
between men and women for the next century.
</P>
<P>
-- China wants to expand its international engineering
contracting business, and will further open its construction
market.  
</P>
