<HEADLINE> Foreign-funded Companies in Southern China Doing Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, October 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 7,848
foreign-funded companies in the city of Shenzhen, the first
special economic zone in south China, have made profits of 18.82
billion yuan so far this year, 3.8 times their losses.
</P>
<P>
A study of foreign-funded companies found that 1.1 percent of
them have stopped production temporarily and that most
money-losing companies are still at an investment stage.
</P>
<P>
The 7,848 companies have a combined investment of 28 billion
U.S. dollars, with overseas capital accounting for close to 12
billion dollars, or one percent more than what they had agreed to
invest.
</P>
<P>
However, some of the companies still have not met the
investment amount specified in their contracts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
