<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Aluminum Business Doing Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, October 27 (Xinhua) -- China's giant Pingguo Aluminum
Co. in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has made good results
in its first three years of operation, with a combined output
value of 5.1 billion yuan (about 600 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project, which cost of 4.3 billion yuan,
started operation in September 1995. A company spokesman said
that high quality bauxite, advanced equipment, and scientific
management allow the project to go smoothly.
</P>
<P>
He said that the company produced 103,000 tons of aluminum
ingots and 33,500 tons of oxidized aluminum in 1997, exceeding its
designed production capacity by three percent and 16.67 percent,
respectively. Both the products are selling well.
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months, the company's average daily output of
oxidized aluminum exceeded 1,000 tons, surpassing the designed
production capacity by 27 percent.
</P>
<P>
The 4.2-billion-yuan company has so for produced 313,900 tons
of aluminum ingots and 88,000 tons of oxidized aluminum, and paid
a total of 181.59 million yuan in taxes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
