<HEADLINE> Dow Down 20 Amid Rises of Other Market Indicators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 26 (Xinhua) -- U.S. blue-chip stocks closed
lower on Monday but small company and technology shares posted
remarkable gains.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 20.08 to 8432.21,
extending Friday's 80-point loss which reversed a seven-session
winning streak mostly as a result of the interest cut by the
Federal Reserve on October 15.
</P>
<P>
The 30-big-company index lost 44 points and regained 68 earlier
today, but it could not hold the rise before the close, due to
continuing profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
On broader market front, the Russell 2000 index of smaller
companies rose 5.67 in a ninth consecutive winning session to
372.07. The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 31.12 to
1724.98.
</P>
<P>
On the New York Stock Exchange, advancers beat decliners 4-3
with trading volume down to 600 million shares from 632 million
previously.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 0.19 to 530.01 and the American
Stock Exchange composite index rose 6.34 to 634.55. 
