<HEADLINE> Mandela to Meet Nigerian Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 26 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela is due to visit Nigeria, and meet the country's
top leader General Abdulsalam Abubakar Thursday, the president's
office announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will discuss regional and continental matters,
presidential aide Parks Mankahlana told the press, but he did not
give details.
</P>
<P>
In addition to his Nigerian tour, Mandela will also travel to
Namibia Wednesday to meet his Namibian counterpart Sam Nujoma as
part of his latest bid for a peaceful settlement to the crisis in
the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
