together with Zimbabwe, Angola and Chad. Kabila accuses Rwanda
and Uganda of invading to support the rebels and he and his
allies refuse to have direct talks with the rebels who occupy
vast territory in the east of the country.
</P>
<P>
Mandela favors settlement of the Congo (K) crisis through
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Business Day, a Johannesburg-based newspaper, reported Monday
that Mandela was also preparing to meet rebel leaders engaged in
a fight against President Kabila, as diplomatic efforts to find a
peaceful solution to the Congo conflict gear up. 
