<HEADLINE> EU Hails Israel-Palestine Peace Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The European Union described
on Monday the peace deal between Israel and Palestine as a
demonstration of courage and sense of responsibility by Benjamin
Netanyahu and Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of EU member states agreed during their
council meeting on Monday that the Israel-Palestine peace deal was
a breakthrough that has opened the door to the early resumption of
the negotiations on permanent status as foreseen in the Oslo
Accord and the implementation of outstanding commitments under the
interim agreement.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers said in a written statement released
after the meeting that the 15-nation union welcomed the forward
movement in the Mideast peace process and looks forward to the
speedy implementation of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
But a sustained political commitment is needed from all parties
concerned, added the foreign ministers, as well as the
determination to resist extremists and others wanting to frustrate
progress toward peace.
</P>
<P>
The EU foreign ministers reiterated the union's firm commitment
to a just and comprehensive settlement in the Middle East based on
the Madrid and Oslo agreements.
</P>
<P>
The European Union, the foreign ministers promised, will
continue its considerable economic and technical assistance to the
Mideast peace process. 
</P>
