<HEADLINE> UN Says Review Not to Come Until Iraq Resumes Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council on Monday stressed that It would not conduct the
Comprehensive review on Iraq until Iraq resumes cooperation with
the United Nations arms inspectors.
</P>
<P>
Jeremy Greenstock, President of the Security Council, made the
remarks after the Council met on Iraq this morning.
</P>
<P>
"The review will start until Iraq has fulfilled the conditions
of Resolution 1194, " Greenstock said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the resolution, Iraq is required to
dismantle all its weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Iraq announced to suspend cooperation with the United Nations
Special Commission in charge of scraping Iraq's prohibited weapons
on August 5, a move the Security Council called totally
unacceptable. The Council on September 9 decided to suspend its
regular review mes cooperation with the United Nations arms
inspectors.  
</P>
