<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Sea Channel Linking UAE, Iraq to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 26 (Xinhua) -- The first sea lane between
the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and Iraq since the 1991 Gulf War
will open to navigation early November.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Monday from Dubai quoted Director General
of the Dubai Ports Sultan Bin-Salim as saying that the line links
UAE's Dubai port and Iraq's Umm-Alkasr.
</P>
<P>
Bin-Salim said the Dubai Ports Administration submitted a
request to the U.N. in September, 1997, for opening the
500-nautical-mile sea lane and the U.N. approved the request
later.
</P>
<P>
A weekly liner will set sail from Dubai for Umm-Alkasr every
Saturday and returns on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The start of liners aims to facilitate cargo and passenger
transport, taking into consideration the U.N.-Iraqi oil-for-food
deal, which allows Iraq to sell limited amount of oil to buy food
and medicine.
</P>
<P>
The luggage of the passengers will be confined to the items
that the U.N. allows access to Iraq, Bin-Salim said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
