<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100GMT, October 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 26 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami has said that the recent accord signed by Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) and Israel was harmful to Arab
countries, the daily Iran News reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Receiving visiting Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq al-Sharaa,
who arrived here Sunday afternoon, Khatami said that the deal
would not enhance regional peace and security, but it was
detrimental to all independent Arab countries, particularly the
Palestinians. (BC-Iran-Khatami-Palestine)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Syrian Foreign Minister Forouq al-Sharaa said in Tehran
on Monday that normalization of ties between Damascus and Ankara
should result in the settlement of all disputes between them.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sharaa made the remark at the end of his two-day visit to Iran,
the official news agency IRNA reported. (BC-Iran-Syria-FM)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli police Tuesday is investigating the fatal
shooting of a Jewish settler in the West Bank city of Hebron,
local TV reports said.
</P>
<P>
The man, who had been shot in the neck, was thrown out of a
moving car in the Israeli-controlled part of the city on Monday
afternoon, Palestinian witnesses said. (BC-Hebron-Shooting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli central bank announced on Monday that it
will increase the interest rates for the first time this year in a
bid to check the devaluation of the shekel.
</P>
<P>
Bank of Israel Governor Jacob Frenkel said in Jerusalem that
the key lending rate will rise by 2 percentage points to 11.5
percent as of November 1.
</P>
<P>
Frenkel said that it was necessary to take such a step in order
to stabilize the foreign currency markets. (BC-Israel-Bank-Rate)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Lebanese Foreign Minister Fares Boueiz Monday
criticized the Palestinian-Israeli peace deal signed in
Washington, saying Lebanon will never have such an agreement with
the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
This is not a victory for the Palestinians in particular and
the Arabs in general as the settlement was reached after the
Palestinians agreed to the Israeli conditions, he said.
(BC-Lebanon-Peace Deal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Palestinian National Authority Chairman Yasser
Arafat arrived in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, Monday to discuss with
Saudi leaders the just-concluded Palestinian-Israeli agreement.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian ambassador to Riyadh Mustafa Deeb told the Kuwait
News Agency that Arafat would also discuss with Saudi King Fahd
Ibn Abdul-Aziz the second phase of the Oslo agreement concerning
the establishment of an independent Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
Deeb said that Arafat would seek Saudi support for the
declaration of Palestinian statehood next May. (BC-Saudi
Arabia-Arafat-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on
Monday survived an attempt to unseat his government after he
signed a breakthrough peace deal with the Palestinians last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Knesset (parliament) defeated a no-confidence motion in the
government tabled by the far-right party Moledet, by a vote of
21-8.
</P>
<P>
Most of the Knesset members did not participate in the voting.
(BC-Israel-No-Confidence Motion) 
</P>
</TEXT>
